# Copy to .env.local and fill in. .env.local is git-ignored.
#
# All values are OPTIONAL — the template builds and runs with no
# credentials at all. The /api/track endpoint then returns 204 and
# events are silently dropped. Wire these up only when you actually
# want to ship analytics.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ClickHouse — used for cookie-less event tracking on the LP.
# Easiest path: ClickHouse Cloud free tier at https://clickhouse.cloud
#   1) Sign up → create a "Production" service (1GB free)
#   2) Copy the HTTPS endpoint into CLICKHOUSE_URL
#   3) Use the default user "default" + the auto-generated password
#   4) Run db/migrations/001_events.sql in the SQL console once
#
# For self-hosting via Docker:
#   docker run -d --name clickhouse -p 8123:8123 \
#     clickhouse/clickhouse-server:latest
# Then CLICKHOUSE_URL=http://localhost:8123, CLICKHOUSE_USER=default,
# CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD= (empty by default for local).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CLICKHOUSE_URL=
CLICKHOUSE_USER=
CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD=
CLICKHOUSE_DATABASE=default
CLICKHOUSE_EVENTS_TABLE=events
